org.mindswap.owl
Class OWLObjectConverterRegistry

java.lang.Object
  org.mindswap.owl.OWLObjectConverterRegistry

public class OWLObjectConverterRegistry
extends java.lang.Object

Global singleton registry for all OWLObjectConverter. There are two ways how to register converters. First, directly using the methods provided by this class. Second, by implementing OWLObjectConverterProvider and adding such implementations as service providers; for details on how to do so see ServiceFinder.

This class is thread safe, using ConcurrentHashMap as the backing data structure. However, OWL object converter registered here may not be thread safe themselves! Consequently, modifications of them (if possible) may require appropriate synchronizations means.

extendByConverter

public <T extends OWLObject> void extendByConverter(java.lang.Class<T> target,
                                                    OWLObjectConverter<? extends T> converter)
Special type of registering some OWL object converter. The method checks if a converter for the target type was already registered. If so, it will check if the associated converter is a CombinedOWLConverter. If this is the case then the given converter will be added to the combined converter. Otherwise, the existing converter will be replaced by a new combined converter containing the existing converter and the given one.

Parameters:
target - The target Java class.
converter - The converter to add.

registerConverter

public <T extends OWLObject> OWLObjectConverter<T> registerConverter(java.lang.Class<T> target,
                                                                     OWLObjectConverter<T> converter)
Register some OWL object converter that is able to determine if some OWLObject can be viewed as the target type, and that implements the conversion procedure.

Note that ListConverter need to be registered using registerListConverter(ListVocabulary, ListConverter).

Parameters:
target - The target Java class.
converter - The converter that can be used to convert some OWLObject into the target class.
Returns:
Previous converter associated to the target Java class, or null if there was no converter registered.

registerListConverter

public <T extends OWLValue> ListConverter<T> registerListConverter(ListVocabulary<T> vocabulary,
                                                                   ListConverter<T> converter)
Register some OWL list converter that is able to check and convert to OWLList according to the properties defined by the given list vocabulary.

Parameters:
vocabulary - The vocabulary used by corresponding lists.
converter - The converter that is able to determine if a OWLIndividual has the properties that are required in order to view it as a OWL list, and that implements the conversion procedure.
Returns:
Previous converter associated to the vocabulary, or null if there was no converter registered.
